wfFrDlcmiTable.name: wfFrDlcmiTable
wfFrDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface

wfFrDlcmiEntry.name: wfFrDlcmiEntry
wfFrDlcmiEntry.description: The parameters for a particular Data Link Connection Management Interface

wfFr1DlcmiDelete.name: wfFr1DlcmiDelete
wfFr1DlcmiDelete.description: Indication to delete this frame relay interface

wfFr1DlcmiDisable.name: wfFr1DlcmiDisable
wfFr1DlcmiDisable.description: Indicates when a dlcmi entry is to be enabled or disabled.

wfFr1DlcmiState.name: wfFr1DlcmiState
wfFr1DlcmiState.description: The current state of Frame Relay. The not present state is not actually valid except when the record is first added. It is included for consistency.

wfFr1DlcmiCircuit.name: wfFr1DlcmiCircuit
wfFr1DlcmiCircuit.description: Instance identifier. The circuit number of this entry

wfFr1DlcmiManagementType.name: wfFr1DlcmiManagementType
wfFr1DlcmiManagementType.description: This variable indicates which Data Link Connection Management scheme is active (and by implication, what DLCI it uses).

wfFr1DlcmiStatus.name: wfFr1DlcmiStatus
wfFr1DlcmiStatus.description: Indicates the status of the interface. FR1_STATUS_START is the state during rebooting or initial start of circuit FR1_STATUS_RUNNING1 is the sate after the circuit is up (either LMI successful or there is no DLCMI and the system just comes up). FR1_STATUS_FAULT is a transient state indicating that errors have caused the circuit to be disabled until DLCMI recovery. FR1_STATUS_RECOVERED indicates that an the system has been in the FR_STATUS_FAULT mode before, but has since recovered.

wfFr1DlcmiAddress.name: wfFr1DlcmiAddress
wfFr1DlcmiAddress.description: This states which address format is in use on the FR interface. The default is Q922

wfFr1DlcmiAddressLen.name: wfFr1DlcmiAddressLen
wfFr1DlcmiAddressLen.description: This variable states the address length in octets. In the case of Q922 format, the length indicates the entire length of the address includeding the control portion.

wfFr1DlcmiPollingInterval.name: wfFr1DlcmiPollingInterval
wfFr1DlcmiPollingInterval.description: The number of seconds between successive status enquiry messages

wfFr1DlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.name: wfFr1DlcmiFullEnquiryInterval
wfFr1DlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.description: The number of status enquiry intervals that pass before issuance of a full status enquiry message.

wfFr1DlcmiErrorThreshold.name: wfFr1DlcmiErrorThreshold
wfFr1DlcmiErrorThreshold.description: This is the maximum number of unanswered Status Enquiries the equipment shall accept before declaring the interface down.

wfFr1DlcmiMonitoredEvents.name: wfFr1DlcmiMonitoredEvents
wfFr1DlcmiMonitoredEvents.description: This is the number of status polling intervals over which the error threshold is counted. For example, if within 'MonitoredEvents' number of events the station receives 'ErrorThreshold' number of errors, the interface is marked as down.

wfFr1DlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.name: wfFr1DlcmiMaxSupportedVCs
wfFr1DlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.description: The maximum number of Virtual Circuits allowed for this interface. Usually dictated by the Frame Relay network. The system sets this initially.

wfFr1DlcmiMulticast.name: wfFr1DlcmiMulticast
wfFr1DlcmiMulticast.description: This indicates whether the frame relay provider offers a multicast

wfFr1DlcmiSeqCount.name: wfFr1DlcmiSeqCount
wfFr1DlcmiSeqCount.description: This station's sequence counter. It represents the next value to send.

wfFr1DlcmiLastReceived.name: wfFr1DlcmiLastReceived
wfFr1DlcmiLastReceived.description: The sequence number just received from the switch.

wfFr1DlcmiPassiveSeqCount.name: wfFr1DlcmiPassiveSeqCount
wfFr1DlcmiPassiveSeqCount.description: This station's sequence counter for answering status enquiry.

wfFr1DlcmiPassiveReceived.name: wfFr1DlcmiPassiveReceived
wfFr1DlcmiPassiveReceived.description: The sequence number just received from the enquring station.

wfFr1DlcmiPolls.name: wfFr1DlcmiPolls
wfFr1DlcmiPolls.description: This is the counter of where we are in the polling cycle.

wfFr1DlcmiAlarmTimer.name: wfFr1DlcmiAlarmTimer
wfFr1DlcmiAlarmTimer.description: This is a counter of 1/2 second timeouts. When it reaches 2 x the polling interval, an enquiry message is sent.

wfFr1ErrType.name: wfFr1ErrType
wfFr1ErrType.description: Indicate the type of the last specific monitored error.

wfFr1ErrData.name: wfFr1ErrData
wfFr1ErrData.description: Contains as much of the error packet as possible.

wfFr1ErrTime.name: wfFr1ErrTime
wfFr1ErrTime.description: The time the last error occurred.

wfFr1ErrDiscards.name: wfFr1ErrDiscards
wfFr1ErrDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames dropped because of format or other errors or because the VC was not known.

wfFr1ErrDrops.name: wfFr1ErrDrops
wfFr1ErrDrops.description: The number of outbound frames dropped. Usually this is due the specified DLCI being unknown or a broadcast packet is too long

wfFrCircuitTable.name: wfFrCircuitTable
wfFrCircuitTable.description: Frame Relay Circuit table gives information about a virtual circuits.

wfFrCircuitEntry.name: wfFrCircuitEntry
wfFrCircuitEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Circuit table.

wfFr1CircuitDelete.name: wfFr1CircuitDelete
wfFr1CircuitDelete.description: Indication to delete this frame relay interface.

wfFr1CircuitNumber.name: wfFr1CircuitNumber
wfFr1CircuitNumber.description: Instance identifier. The circuit number of this interface.

wfFr1CircuitDlci.name: wfFr1CircuitDlci
wfFr1CircuitDlci.description: Instance identifier. This indicates which virtual circuit.

wfFr1CircuitState.name: wfFr1CircuitState
wfFr1CircuitState.description: Indicates the state of the particular virtual circuit.

wfFr1CircuitStateSet.name: wfFr1CircuitStateSet
wfFr1CircuitStateSet.description: User access for setting the state of a virtual circuit

wfFr1CircuitReceivedFECNs.name: wfFr1CircuitReceivedFECNs
wfFr1CircuitReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received indicating forward congestion.

wfFr1CircuitReceivedBECNs.name: wfFr1CircuitReceivedBECNs
wfFr1CircuitReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received indicating backward congestion.

wfFr1CircuitSentFrames.name: wfFr1CircuitSentFrames
wfFr1CircuitSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit.

wfFr1CircuitSentOctets.name: wfFr1CircuitSentOctets
wfFr1CircuitSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit.

wfFr1CircuitReceivedFrames.name: wfFr1CircuitReceivedFrames
wfFr1CircuitReceivedFrames.description: The number of frames received from this virtual circuit.

wfFr1CircuitReceivedOctets.name: wfFr1CircuitReceivedOctets
wfFr1CircuitReceivedOctets.description: The number of octets received from this virtual circuit.

wfFr1CircuitCreationTime.name: wfFr1CircuitCreationTime
wfFr1CircuitCreationTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the vc was created.

wfFr1CircuitLastTimeChange.name: wfFr1CircuitLastTimeChange
wfFr1CircuitLastTimeChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when last there was a change in vc state.

wfFr1CircuitCommittedBurst.name: wfFr1CircuitCommittedBurst
wfFr1CircuitCommittedBurst.description: Indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval. Wellfleet does not presently support this.

wfFr1CircuitExcessBurst.name: wfFr1CircuitExcessBurst
wfFr1CircuitExcessBurst.description: Indicates teh maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will attempt to deliver over the measurement interval. Wellfleet does not presently support this.

wfFr1CircuitThroughput.name: wfFr1CircuitThroughput
wfFr1CircuitThroughput.description: This is the average number of 'Frame Relay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement interval. Wellfleet does not presently support this.

wfFr1CircuitMulticast.name: wfFr1CircuitMulticast
wfFr1CircuitMulticast.description: Indicates whether this DLCI is used for multicast or single destination.

wfFr1CircuitDiscards.name: wfFr1CircuitDiscards
wfFr1CircuitDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames discarded because of format errors, because the VC is inactive or because the protocol was not registered for this circuit.

wfFr1CircuitDrops.name: wfFr1CircuitDrops
wfFr1CircuitDrops.description: Indicates how many outbound frames were dropped. Usually these are dropped because the VC is not active.

wfFr1CircuitSubCct.name: wfFr1CircuitSubCct
wfFr1CircuitSubCct.description: Circuit number to use for this VC when configured in hybrid (for bridging) or direct access (VC as a circuit) mode.

wfFr1CircuitMode.name: wfFr1CircuitMode
wfFr1CircuitMode.description: The mode of the given VC. GROUP - treats the VC as one of many vc's on a circuit. HYBRID - treats the VC as one of many vc's on a circuit for protocol traffic, but as a separate circuit for bridging. DIRECT - treats the VC as a separate circuit for all applications.
